div.p:
1. Labor Oeconomicus or mechanicus, the labour of mechanicks, as we call them, or handicrafts-men; of this the Apoſtle ſpeaks, Let him that stole ſteale no more; 
                        Eph. 4.28. 
                        but rather let him labour, working with his hands the thing which is good.

That ſuppoſe it be ſo, we may find in  Scripture meat-offerings to be burnt with fire; thus you read concerning Gideons offering; 
                        Judg. 6.19. 21. the ſame we read concerning Manoahs offering. 
                        Judg. 13. 19, 20.
